name: TIMsanity
description: While there's been intense internal debate about this controversial trade here at 27up27down, there's no doubt that TIMsanity has crashed into the tri-state area sports market like a bat out of... well, Heaven I guess. Brace yourselves people, and gear up for the ride.

name: Mets Keep Calm and Carry On
description:
To borrow from Winston Churchill:

"I have, myself, full confidence that if all do their duty, if nothing is neglected, and if the best arrangements are made, as they are being made, we shall prove ourselves once again able to defend our NL East prominence, to ride out the storm of injury, and to outlive the menace of Philadelphia, if necessary for years, if necessary alone.

At any rate, that is what we are going to try to do. That is the resolve of Mets fans-every man of them. That is the will of the fanbase and the nation. The offense and the defense, linked together in their cause and in their need, will defend to the death their native Citi Field soil, aiding each other like good comrades to the utmost of their strength.

Even though large tracts of the National League and many old and famous franchises have fallen or may fall into the grip of the Phillies and all the odious apparatus of the Atlanta Braves, we shall not flag or fail. We shall go on to the end, we shall fight at home, we shall fight in San Fransisco next to the seas and oceans, we shall fight with growing confidence and growing strength in St. Louis, we shall defend Long Island, whatever the cost may be, we shall fight on the beaches of Miami, we shall fight in Dodger Stadium, we shall fight in Wrigley Field and in Cincinatti, we shall fight on that stupid hill the Astros have in center field; we shall never surrender, and even if, which I do not for a moment believe, this season or a large part of it were subjugated and starving, then our Mets fans beyond the seas, armed and guarded by Gary Keith and Ron, would carry on the struggle, until, in God's good time, the New York Mets, with all their power and might, step forth to the rescue and the liberation of the old."

name: Mets Takeover: Phillies
description:
What better way to annoy the opposition than by co-opting their logo? Watch that high-five from an unsuspecting rival fan turn into a fist of confusion and rage before your very eyes!

WARNING: Only for the die-hardingest of die-hard fans. (Not recommended for use in Philadelphia)

name: New York Jetropolitans
description:
Do you love the Mets?

Do you love the Jets?

Then you must also have a soft spot in your heart for soul-crushing losses, public relations disasters, and a sports inferiority complex the size of Rex Ryan's waistband.

So why not wear it with pride? Because as a fan of both Gang Green and Gang No Green you know that misery loves company.

M-E-T-S JETS JETS JETS!!!

name: Word to Your Mothma
description:
There are a ton of clever Star Wars related shirts out there, and here's another one! "Word to Your Mothma" celebrates the original Rebel leader and shows off both fashion sense and intergalactic feminism.

Many Bothans died to bring you this t-shirt.
